        </a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
      <p>As an American, you need to pick one of 12 categories of authorized travel to Cuba. The broadest category you may currently use to travel independently to Cuba is the Support for the Cuban People category. You will need to abide by the regulations and participate in activities that are in the spirit of the category. To summarize:</p>
      <p>•  An independent traveler can travel under this category. </p>
      <p>•  A traveler is required to provide support for the Cuban people and promote independent activity intended to strengthen civil society in Cuba.</p>
      <p>•  A traveler is required to engage in Support for the Cuban People activities consistent with a full-time schedule. These types of activities include: Meeting with local businessmen, artists, tobacco manufacturers and people who own their own business; explore independent museums; independent markets; dance classes; meeting and engaging with musicians at a show; art shows; discuss Cuban society with locals.</p>
      <p>•  A traveler must avoid all transactions with a GAESA-owned (military-owned) business.</p>

      All our programs fall under this category. These are some of the activities that are included and count toward Support for the Cuban People:
<p>1.  Stay at casa particular (B&B homestay) when roundtrips are arranged by Havana True Colors.</p>
<p>2.  Support and engage with local business and independent entrepreneurs like artists, musicians, food vendors, restaurant owners, B&B homestay owners, etc. Whatever your interests, you can find a way to support the Cuban people.</p>
<p>3.  Eat at local restaurant or paladares.</p>
<p>4.  Avoid transactions at military-owned business.</p>
<p>To fit into this category, several programs have been designed and all engage in compliant activities over enough hours to fulfill a full-time schedule. We are open to customized your experience upon request while assisting to ensure that your stay is compliant with the new travel requirements.</p>
<p>This has been stated multiple times, both in the announcement and in the released documentation and Marco Rubio, who was leading this policy change, explicitly outlines how Americans can travel to Cuba under Support for the Cuban People category.</p>
<p>Before new regulations announced by the Trump Administration went into effect, many travelers were able to choose the People to People Educational category. Under the new Cuba travel regulations, a traveler can only choose the People to People category if they are traveling with a group package tour, meaning you can no longer travel independently under that category.</p>

